rComments: Avoid this prof at all costs. The course does have free participation marks, but her exams and essays are pure hell. She will give more effort into penalizing for the most stupid and irrelevant mistakes more than giving points for stuff we learn or should apply. She will tell you that she is not a tough grader and that is the biggest lie ever.

Elaine is overall a great professor. I had her for ENG 1100 and her lectures were pre-recorded as modules, giving you flexibility with your schedule. The content of her lectures were quite resourceful, giving useful information. She also added a touch of humour to them. Elaine was very easy to contact, and would always answer emails very quickly.

Ms. Bailey is absolutely the worse professor i have ever meet. Her lactures are unnecesary and useless. I watched 4 of the videos because her assignments have no relationship with what she taught. The TA of her class are rigorous grader. They will grade your paper with Ms. Bailey together and take your points away as possible in ridiculous way.

She's a really nice person. I wasn't in her discussion group section (I had a TA's section) so I didn't get too much of a feel for her actual teaching style but when I did hear her lecture it was pretty interesting. She clearly cares a lot about her students as individuals and wants people to understand.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Graded by few things', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: She was not that bad of a teacher; I just did not enjoy how she taught the class. There was very little interaction, other than her 4-5, 20-minute lecture videos and weekly zoom discussion (which her TA did). Her grading was alright; she did not give too much feedback on how to improve our writing.

Prof Bailey is a sweet prof and she's always accessible out of class! She is willing to go over exam/quizzes with you and gives great feedback! Her grading is very clear and helpful. English is not my first language, but her lessons (concise and separated by topic) are easy to understand and it was still possible for me to succeed in her class.

Super nice prof handed in my final late and she took it anyways. Very easy class, she teaches it well, explains well, and quizzes are easy. In high school, I got mid to high 70s in English, and with her, I get much higher, there's no homework other than the 5-6 quizzes we had that were available for weeks on end.

For a class with typically boring content, she really does her best to make it interesting for her students. Responds quickly to emails and will arrange a meeting to help you at any time without judgement. I was really surprised to have the chance to write about a scientific topic in an English class for my final that actually pertains to my major!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Elaine is nice and answers her emails. The TA's are extremely hard markers. I put everything I had into this class and it wasn't good enough. It ruined my straight A's. I honestly have no idea how people are successful with this course because my first language is English and I've always done well and this has ruined my confidence. GOOD LUCK!

This class was great! The essays she covered were very interesting and she made concepts very easy to understand. She is very approachable and friendly. There were no surprises, I didn't have to attend class (it was asynchronous and online for 2020 fall term), the workload was tolerable, and I didn't have to refer to the textbook very much.

Didn't love her as a prof but the class was super easy - finished my assignments with minimal work and got 90s. I barely went to class and was fine. Her organization of an online course is a bit confusing.

It was an asynchronous course so I never actually talked to Prof. Bailey, but she breaks up all the lectures into smaller parts to make them easier to watch which is really nice. Also all the assignments are pretty straight forward and there aren't that many too if you have her I'd stick with it.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: Class was extremely boring but attendance is mandatory because it's marked. Essays and assignments were very easy. She's honestly a mediocre prof, not bad but not great either. Definitely read the books if you want a good grade, it'll make the assignments easier. She responds very fast to emails, which I really appreciated

I suggest you don't listen to the other reviews. Her lectures were dull af but I only showed up for attendance marks. As long as you read everything and have some understanding of English this course will be an easy grade boost. I found her to be an easy marker because I didn't put much effort into the assignments but still got good grades.
Don't go to the lectures, it's pointless. Just go to the DGDs for your participation marks. If found her to be a hard marker, but I am also not the best at English.

Dr Bailey treats the students as if they havent been taking English classes the entire time theyve been in school and acts as if no on has written an essay before. The class is an easy A but unfortunately you have to show up to all the DGDs because attendance is taken for a mark and theyre extremely excruciating.

Dr Bailey is quite blunt and will tell you if your work is garbage but she is pretty good about answering personal questions about your essay. The lectures are absolutely useless, don't bother going, just go to the DGD. My lecture and DGD were right after each other and she always ended super early which was nice!

Easy class. She is a great prof. Responds to emails quickly, and is kind. She really challenges you to become a better writer, so shes not the easiest grader, however she gives tons of feedback along the way. I would take a class with her again! She provides the readings and suggests you buy a textbook. We did not use the textbook often though.
Easy class, only have 3 essays to write all year and are all pretty easy. She's nice and teaches well.

Dr. Bailey is a tough marker, it's her way or the highway when it comes to getting a good grade. I took my paper to the academic writing centre and the TA told me I'd easily get an A, ended up getting a 73%. Attend DGDs as attendance is taken and quizzes are frequently held. She tells you to buy the textbook but thats useless. Light workload.

Boring and dry lectures, everything could be taught in a week and she rambles often. Some lectures even taught the exact same material. Powerpoints are not very organized. Unfair essay marker and focuses too much on the thesis (if it is not 'her way', it is 'wrong') Gives clear outline for what's expected for midterm and final DGD's were helpful

Professor Bailey is very kind and helpful to her students. She is quick to answer emails and is willing to stay after class with any questions you need answered. The course itself can be boring at times if youve taken a pre-u english class in high school, but the readings were interesting and shes a fair marker. Would take a course of hers again!

Go to DGDs for the insultingly easy grammar quizzes and don't bother with her lectures; they're a waste of time and she'll post them on blackboard eventually anyway. Mediocre at best with average marking difficulty. Honestly felt like a bird course to me; other than the two major essays I didn't do a single thing for it.

You get to improve your grade with the grammar quizzes and two essays. She gives clear criteria about the final essay, and she can help you if you have any problems writing it. The content was dry (grammar and how to structure an essay), but she made the lecture classes easier to bear.
She is a tough marker, at least with the essays.

She was a super nice prof but the lectures were unorganized, I found myself typing a ridiculous amount during one lecture. Attendance is 10% but you can only get an 8 if you don't speak. It's not an easy A but she's for sure not there to sink you either

Her policy is that if you don't have a good thesis, the rest of the essay isn't even worth anything and you won't get above a B so work hard on the thesis! Course content is boring and lectures are useless if you have a basic understanding of essay writing. DGDs are important and quizzes are easy but not worth much overall. Make sure to do readings

This teacher screams mediocrity her lectures are tedious, and she only corrects the final papers. Her TA was a tough grader. She talks about narrowing a thesis often without really giving many examples. She fails to explain the final exam

I LOVED this class :) The assigned reading material was very interesting. The prof was good as well; she was available to answer questions and her feedback was helpful.  1 TIP: ATTEND the DGDs (discussion groups)! Often I found the DGDs to be even more beneficial than the lectures; attend the DGDs faithfully, it's totally worth it.

The course itself is boring, redundant and frankly  unnecessary, especially if you've taken a pre-university English class in high school and did well. I didn't really learn anything new. The grammar quizzes are a joke. Bailey is a good prof though, she was available during office hours and gave good feedback in the early stages of each essay.

Dr. Bailey really cares for her students and is really understanding if you have issues during the semester, but the material is dry and she teaches it really dry. Her marking is really "knit picky", you'll loose a percent for pretty much each mistake. Her discussion groups are boring and useless.

Very unclear with what she will grade on essays, grades essays very hard, when I missed a class I asked her if she could send me the powerpoints or go over with me what I missed and she refused the former, then took me aside for 2 minutes to explain the latter (which clearly wasn't enough if it was a 1.25 hour lecture).

With her, it was a very tedious class with the main focus on grammar. Though she tried to be stimulating and helpful she wasn't. Worst though, her marking was very hard. Coming from highschool (a very good one) I had always gotten A+ but with her no matter how much effort and changes I made unless you write it the way SHE would've you only got Bs.

Prof. Bailey is an excellent professor. She cares deeply for the success of her students and will accommodate your need based on how you learn. She is also very knowledgeable about the format needed for essay-writing at UofO. Thank you for a great semester!

Bailey is an excellent professor, it was a pleasure being in her ENG1100 class. Unfortunately with the subject matter, the class can at times be a little tedious, but this is not her fault. Additionally, the readings Bailey selects are very interesting, and I would highly recommend this class for anyone needing to hone their essay writing skills.

At times he makes one word seem the length of five. Her classes are really slow and boring. I would take her class again for an easy A but it's the hardest A you'll ever get because going to class is a chore and a half.

Very easy class - stuff we learned in early high school. Bailey is a very nice and approachable teacher, however. DGDs are mandatory but they're easy marks and the quizzes are incredibly easy. Lectures are skippable unless you have no basic understanding of essay formats and English grammar.
This class is extremely boring, the DGD is mandatory, but lectures aren't. I only went to the first few lectures then stopped, my grade wasn't affect by this.The class is easy.
Knows her stuff, but classes are extremely boring. Workshops are mandatory and easy grades. She's pretty particular about how you write, just follow what she suggests and you should be fine.

I like her, but her classes are usually pretty boring. Students never pay attention and it gets pretty distracting.. the discussion group with our TA is a complete joke though. He doesn't know what he's talking about & nobody respects him. He always says something along the lines of "or something I don't really know but you'll learn it eventually"

Bailey is a good person, but a very boring professor. The lecture sections are long and drawn-out and deathly boring. You dont really learn much during the whole course, but mandatory to go to each "workshop" section. She is very helpful and personal though!
She gives generous marks but her class is boing. (Don't recommend for Saturday course..but I think she prefers Sat. to teach...) She is kind but somehow very strict.
Nice, helpful, clear, easy to understand... Seems she tries to sound British at times, which is puzzling.
She comes off as being stuck up. She had a hard time getting the class to talk.
Fairly interesting reading list. Good thing 'cause the class was a snore-fest. Learn how to stretch one sentence into five and you'll do fine.
very monotone, not interesting as a professor.
Good prof, in my opinion.  Most of the reading is pretty good, but our class (myself included) was silent when she tried to start conversations.  I think she wanted me.
Seems to think she's teaching high school. Tries to converse rather than lecture
Clearly, teaching is a real chore.
No Comments
we deserve someone better
No Comments
She seems either depressed or repressed.
